WEBVTT

00:10.010 --> 00:12.429
<i>- Previously, on "Dare Me"...</i>

00:12.512 --> 00:13.763
- We can't be here.

00:13.847 --> 00:17.142
We can never have been here
at all.

00:17.225 --> 00:19.602
Your shoes--Addy,
where are your cheer shoes?

00:20.812 --> 00:23.440
- You give her too much power.
Stop feeding the beast.

00:24.649 --> 00:25.984
- [knocking]
- Beth?

00:26.067 --> 00:27.569
Did somebody
do something to you?

00:27.652 --> 00:29.654
[shutter clicks]

00:29.738 --> 00:31.364
- Colette, are you okay?
What happened?

00:31.448 --> 00:32.657
- We both know
once they start digging

00:32.741 --> 00:34.367
into Sarge Will's
puny little life

00:34.451 --> 00:36.286
they're gonna find
something interesting.

00:36.369 --> 00:38.038
<i>It's like turning over a rock</i>

00:38.121 --> 00:40.373
<i>and all these ugly things</i>
<i>wriggle out.</i>

00:40.457 --> 00:43.251
How come you never choose me?

00:43.334 --> 00:44.794
<i>What does she have</i>
<i>that I don't?</i>

00:44.878 --> 00:46.713
- She isn't you.

00:48.715 --> 00:51.634
<i>[light music]</i>

00:51.718 --> 00:52.927
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:53.011 --> 00:55.680
[shower running]

00:55.764 --> 00:59.225
<i>- I fell into a dream.</i>

00:59.309 --> 01:01.936
<i>A beautiful dream.</i>
[shower stops]

01:02.020 --> 01:05.607
[water drains]

01:05.690 --> 01:07.609
<i>I didn't wanna leave</i>
<i>the dream.</i>

01:07.692 --> 01:10.695
[rain pattering]

01:13.364 --> 01:18.787
[wheel squeaking]
<i>- Addy, where is you Hamsa?</i>

01:18.870 --> 01:20.455
<i>- You're stumbling, Addy.</i>

01:20.538 --> 01:23.792
<i>- It's bad, Addy.</i>

01:23.875 --> 01:25.418
<i>- Addy.</i>

01:25.502 --> 01:31.925
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:32.008 --> 01:33.760
<i>- Addy.</i>
- [gasps]

01:33.843 --> 01:36.846
[panting]

01:38.223 --> 01:45.230
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:46.689 --> 01:49.734
[phone rings]

01:49.818 --> 01:51.820
[sighs]
Hey.

01:51.903 --> 01:54.489
- You better be wearing
your Hamsa today,

01:54.572 --> 01:56.241
'cause shit is going down.

01:56.324 --> 01:58.827
What?

01:58.910 --> 02:01.121
My Hamsa?
<i>- Guess what I'm doing.</i>

02:01.204 --> 02:03.748
Reading the actual newspaper.

02:03.832 --> 02:06.209
I thought the old lady
would faint.

02:06.292 --> 02:09.254
"Do you even know what that is,
darling daughter?"

02:09.337 --> 02:13.049
Oh, the morning wit
in the Cassidy household.

02:13.133 --> 02:14.259
[chuckles]

02:14.342 --> 02:15.718
<i>- What's it say?</i>

02:15.802 --> 02:18.888
<i>- "A police source reported</i>
<i>growing suspicions</i>

02:18.972 --> 02:21.808
<i>"after autopsy results</i>
<i>raised questions</i>

02:21.891 --> 02:25.228
"about the gun's trajectory.

02:25.311 --> 02:28.148
"One source also indicated
gunshot residue tests

02:28.231 --> 02:32.569
<i>on the victim's hands</i>
<i>showed only trace amounts."</i>

02:32.652 --> 02:35.155
Fuck me, Hanlon.

02:35.238 --> 02:37.574
<i>You wait your whole life</i>
<i>for something to happen,</i>

02:37.657 --> 02:41.452
and then, suddenly it does.

02:42.328 --> 02:45.248
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

02:45.331 --> 02:52.338
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:54.465 --> 02:56.384
[inhales]

03:01.681 --> 03:04.559
<i>I never wanted to hurt him--</i>
<i>to hurt Matt.</i>

03:04.642 --> 03:06.352
We--we didn't text,
we didn't talk.

03:06.436 --> 03:09.522
We used this app.
The messages weren't stored.

03:09.606 --> 03:12.984
Now that he's gone,
there's nothing left, Addy.

03:15.069 --> 03:18.990
There's nothing
that connects us.

03:19.073 --> 03:21.159
- What if someone was there
before we were?

03:21.242 --> 03:24.787
- We would've known.

03:24.871 --> 03:27.290
We would've been able to tell.

03:27.373 --> 03:29.459
- The cops can tell.

03:29.542 --> 03:31.628
My mom said they've been
looking at everything.

03:31.711 --> 03:34.672
- Your mom...

03:34.756 --> 03:37.800
she's working on the case?

03:37.884 --> 03:40.345
- Everyone is.
It's a big deal.

03:40.428 --> 03:44.015
Coach, it's getting bigger
every day.

03:45.516 --> 03:48.186
What if they find out about us?

03:49.938 --> 03:52.023
We could just tell them.

03:52.106 --> 03:54.651
Finding a body's not a crime.

03:54.734 --> 03:57.654
<i>[tense music]</i>

03:57.737 --> 03:58.655
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:58.738 --> 04:02.659
- Is that what you want, Addy?

04:02.742 --> 04:05.912
Sitting in
an interrogation room...

04:05.995 --> 04:09.415
telling a cop what you saw...

04:10.833 --> 04:13.002
What you did?

04:17.173 --> 04:20.385
And then telling your mom?

04:24.264 --> 04:27.684
I won't let you
go through that.

04:28.977 --> 04:31.729
I won't.

04:31.813 --> 04:34.190
I know how hard this is.

04:34.274 --> 04:36.442
Hey, it is hard for me, too.

04:36.526 --> 04:39.737
I can't get it out of my head,
any of it.

04:41.114 --> 04:43.491
[sighs]

04:47.370 --> 04:49.580
[exhales]

04:49.664 --> 04:56.671
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:02.844 --> 05:09.851
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:13.938 --> 05:16.190
- No, tell him double
if he'll rush it.

05:16.274 --> 05:19.235
Well, now that Sutton Grove's
finest is done,

05:19.319 --> 05:20.695
we gotta just
throw some bleach in there

05:20.778 --> 05:22.488
and get that baby
rented out again.

05:22.572 --> 05:23.906
Oh, and get the locksmith
in there, too.

05:23.990 --> 05:26.993
We gotta fix that door before
the ghouls start lurking.

05:27.076 --> 05:28.953
[hangs phone up]
Beth Ann.

05:29.037 --> 05:31.748
The prodigal--
or maybe I'm the prodigal

05:31.831 --> 05:33.499
after my shameful conduct

05:33.583 --> 05:34.667
at that restaurant
in Cleveland.

05:34.751 --> 05:36.794
- Skip it.

05:36.878 --> 05:40.173
It's water under
the slowly sinking bridge.

05:40.256 --> 05:44.594
But if we were to say,
quantify it,

05:44.677 --> 05:46.471
how broken up are you, Pops?

05:46.554 --> 05:49.182
- [chuckles]

05:49.265 --> 05:51.017
I don't know.

05:51.100 --> 05:54.896
I did the crimes,
I'll do the time.

06:03.071 --> 06:04.030
Champ, you wanna catch

06:04.113 --> 06:05.448
a second breakfast
with the old man?

06:05.531 --> 06:08.117
The place in the lobby
has really upped their game.

06:08.201 --> 06:10.036
You'll have to pay.
I'm a little light. [chuckles]

06:10.119 --> 06:12.789
- I'm good.
I got everything I need.

06:12.872 --> 06:15.083
- You let me know
if you don't.

06:15.166 --> 06:16.876
Hey, uh,
last game tomorrow night.

06:16.959 --> 06:18.169
I'll be there, of course.

06:18.252 --> 06:21.380
Can you believe we're--
we're finally here?

06:21.464 --> 06:23.424
- I can.

06:23.508 --> 06:25.301
- [clears throat]
Beth Ann, I--I, uh,

06:25.384 --> 06:28.304
I see it, you know?

06:28.387 --> 06:31.057
I see it,
and it takes my breath away--

06:31.140 --> 06:34.352
how good you've gotten.

06:34.435 --> 06:36.354
She made you tougher.
She make you stronger.

06:36.437 --> 06:38.564
- She didn't.

06:38.648 --> 06:41.275
I did.

06:42.193 --> 06:49.200
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:58.417 --> 06:59.836
[bell dings]

06:59.919 --> 07:02.839
<i>[pop music playing</i>
<i>on headphones]</i>

07:02.922 --> 07:09.929
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:47.360 --> 08:50.279
<i>[tense music]</i>

08:50.363 --> 08:57.370
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:21.852 --> 09:24.689
<i>[tense music]</i>

09:24.772 --> 09:25.815
- Uh--

09:25.898 --> 09:29.694
Sorry, I--
I'm on the wrong floor.

09:29.777 --> 09:31.821
- Aren't we all, honey?

09:31.904 --> 09:35.783
It's easy to get lost,
isn't it?

09:35.866 --> 09:38.244
I knew it wasn't suicide.

09:38.327 --> 09:40.162
[chuckles]

09:40.246 --> 09:42.331
Didn't get into it
with the cops.

09:42.415 --> 09:44.709
I hate cops.

09:44.792 --> 09:46.877
Wanna hear my theory?

09:46.961 --> 09:48.588
- Absolutely.

09:53.175 --> 09:55.094
- Serial killer.

09:55.177 --> 09:56.637
Huntin' down Marines.

09:56.721 --> 10:00.057
Everyone's political
these days.

10:00.141 --> 10:02.101
- There's only one Marine,
though.

10:02.184 --> 10:03.311
- Oh, no.

10:03.394 --> 10:06.147
There was always
the other one, hulking around.

10:06.230 --> 10:07.481
Spooky looking one.

10:07.565 --> 10:09.775
Big guy, darty eyes.

10:09.859 --> 10:11.319
Reminded me of my ex.

10:11.402 --> 10:13.154
Well, before he got hauled off

10:13.237 --> 10:15.948
for three to seven
in Chillicothe.

10:16.032 --> 10:17.617
- Well, if there was
a serial killer

10:17.700 --> 10:19.660
targeting Marines,

10:19.744 --> 10:22.580
sounds like he'd be one
well worth taking out.

10:23.956 --> 10:27.293
Crime of passion's
a much more plausible theory.

10:27.376 --> 10:30.212
If you believe what you hear
about that girlfriend.

10:30.296 --> 10:32.506
- The blonde?

10:32.590 --> 10:34.300
Sure.

10:34.383 --> 10:36.010
- She around much?

10:36.093 --> 10:38.804
- Uh--I mind my business.

10:38.888 --> 10:41.474
We all take our comforts
as we may.

10:41.557 --> 10:43.100
Pretty, though.

10:43.184 --> 10:45.394
But twitchy.
Always in a rush.

10:45.478 --> 10:47.396
- You seen her lately?

10:47.480 --> 10:49.649
Like...maybe the night

10:49.732 --> 10:53.402
he shuffled off
this mortal coil?

10:53.486 --> 10:56.697
- Look at you, Sam Spade.
[chuckles]

10:56.781 --> 10:58.866
No, I haven't seen her
in a while.

10:58.949 --> 11:02.244
Oh, she always looked
too high hat for this joint

11:02.328 --> 11:06.457
Figured she had her fun
and moved on.

11:08.209 --> 11:10.628
Didn't I see you here before?

11:10.711 --> 11:12.546
- No.

11:12.630 --> 11:14.507
You must have me confused
with someone else.

11:14.590 --> 11:16.092
- Hm.

11:26.060 --> 11:28.979
<i>[tense music]</i>

11:29.063 --> 11:36.070
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:46.038 --> 11:48.666
<i>[music intensifies]</i>

11:48.749 --> 11:55.756
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:00.469 --> 12:01.929
No.

12:02.012 --> 12:09.019
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:12.273 --> 12:14.733
- Morning, miss.

12:18.112 --> 12:20.573
[chatter]

12:20.656 --> 12:23.576
<i>[tense music]</i>

12:23.659 --> 12:29.165
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:29.248 --> 12:30.458
- [sighs]

12:30.541 --> 12:33.961
I guess somebody's parents
complained.

12:34.044 --> 12:35.212
They think it's morbid.

12:35.296 --> 12:38.007
You know, now that
he was murdered.

12:38.090 --> 12:41.844
- But we don't really know,
do we?

12:41.927 --> 12:44.680
- Well, tell that to them.

12:44.763 --> 12:47.558
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:47.641 --> 12:49.768
- Cops.
- Yeah.

12:49.852 --> 12:52.396
Actual, real detectives.

12:52.480 --> 12:54.982
I wonder who's next.

12:56.400 --> 12:59.653
[bell rings]

13:01.113 --> 13:04.116
<i>[eerie music]</i>

13:20.841 --> 13:25.137
[inhales, exhales]

13:25.221 --> 13:27.848
[doorbell dings]
- Hm.

13:29.558 --> 13:32.686
- Colette French?
- Yes.

13:32.770 --> 13:35.064
- We're hoping you might be
able to answer a few questions.

13:37.191 --> 13:38.234
- Of course.

13:38.317 --> 13:40.110
I'm sorry it's such a mess.

13:40.194 --> 13:43.531
I am usually
much more organized than this.

13:43.614 --> 13:46.867
- Miss French, we tried
to reach you over the phone.

13:46.951 --> 13:48.536
- You--you did?

13:48.619 --> 13:51.247
I--that can't be.
I didn't--

13:51.330 --> 13:52.623
- Your home phone.

13:52.706 --> 13:54.083
- Oh, the landline.

13:54.166 --> 13:55.084
We don't--
- That's the only number

13:55.167 --> 13:56.877
that we had
under your registration.

13:59.713 --> 14:00.923
Florida plates.

14:01.006 --> 14:02.758
Are you just passing
through town, Miss French?

14:02.841 --> 14:04.843
- No.

14:07.346 --> 14:09.974
Look, what--
what is this about?

14:10.057 --> 14:12.017
- It's about the other night.

14:12.101 --> 14:14.687
- Your little misadventure.

14:16.855 --> 14:19.608
- I don't know what you mean.

14:19.692 --> 14:22.403
- You seem a little nervous.

14:22.486 --> 14:24.613
You thought you'd
gotten away with it, huh?

14:27.032 --> 14:29.118
A week ago, Tuesday.

14:32.621 --> 14:34.874
- Last Tuesday?
- Mm-hmm.

14:34.957 --> 14:38.419
Cameras caught everything.
They always do.

14:38.502 --> 14:40.921
- I don't understand--

14:41.005 --> 14:43.549
[creaking]
Matt.

14:43.632 --> 14:45.551
- You the husband?

14:45.634 --> 14:47.261
- Yeah, I'm the husband

14:47.344 --> 14:49.054
who wants to know what
you're doing here with my wife.

14:49.138 --> 14:51.724
- Your wife ran into
a light pole on Revere,

14:51.807 --> 14:52.808
by the liquor store.

14:52.892 --> 14:54.226
Took a bite out of it.

14:54.310 --> 14:56.478
- Cameras caught it.
License plate and all.

14:56.562 --> 14:59.273
That's a misdemeanor.
Evading responsibility.

14:59.356 --> 15:02.693
You know what those light poles
cost taxpayers, huh?

15:02.776 --> 15:04.778
- I'll pay for it.

15:04.862 --> 15:06.530
Uh, I--

15:06.614 --> 15:08.699
I will pay for everything.

15:08.782 --> 15:10.910
Well, thank you, officers.
I'm sorry.

15:10.993 --> 15:13.329
I swear, I didn't think
I'd done any damage.

15:13.412 --> 15:15.497
- 'Cause you never bothered
to look back.

15:15.581 --> 15:17.166
Let that be
a lesson to you, Miss.

15:17.249 --> 15:19.084
There are cameras everywhere.

15:19.168 --> 15:22.421
- I--I promise
I learned my lesson.

15:22.504 --> 15:25.925
- And it's the funniest thing,
that, uh, CCTV footage,

15:26.008 --> 15:27.259
it looked for all the world

15:27.343 --> 15:29.053
like you drove into
that light pole on purpose,

15:29.136 --> 15:32.431
like nothing could stop you.

15:33.307 --> 15:36.894
Well, you have a nice evening.
Both of you.

15:36.977 --> 15:43.984
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:48.906 --> 15:51.659
- I'm gonna need a minute.

15:57.873 --> 16:00.793
<i>[E-Cig's "Cut Your Bangs"]</i>

16:00.876 --> 16:07.883
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:10.177 --> 16:15.891
<i>- ♪ Last night I saw your face</i>
<i>in the hallowed light ♪</i>

16:15.975 --> 16:21.689
<i>♪ You were standing taller</i>
<i>than a mountainside ♪</i>

16:21.772 --> 16:26.902
<i>♪ Your long hair flowed down</i>
<i>in blues and whites ♪</i>

16:26.986 --> 16:31.281
<i>♪ And I just stood there,</i>
<i>bathed in the quiet ♪</i>

16:31.365 --> 16:35.035
<i>♪ No, you say</i>
<i>you'll cut your bangs ♪</i>

16:35.119 --> 16:38.122
<i>♪ I'm calling your bluff ♪</i>

16:38.205 --> 16:43.168
<i>♪ When you lie to me</i>
<i>it's in the small stuff ♪</i>

16:43.252 --> 16:46.046
<i>♪ You say</i>
<i>you'll cut your bangs ♪</i>

16:46.130 --> 16:49.049
<i>♪ I'm calling your bluff ♪</i>

16:49.133 --> 16:53.846
<i>♪ When you lie to me</i>
<i>it's in the small stuff... ♪</i>

16:53.929 --> 16:57.057
[footsteps approaching]

16:57.141 --> 17:00.769
- Don't tell me
you still have that box.

17:00.853 --> 17:04.189
Uh, Bert and his cigars.

17:04.273 --> 17:05.691
What would Freud say?

17:05.774 --> 17:09.361
Cuban by way of Tijuana.
Remember that smell? [laughs]

17:09.445 --> 17:11.905
- Slave labor
and Bain de Soleil?

17:11.989 --> 17:13.574
- [laughs]

17:13.657 --> 17:15.909
We gotta hang that up
down here.

17:15.993 --> 17:17.786
Along with the heads
of your victims.

17:17.870 --> 17:19.955
- Don't think there's room.

17:20.039 --> 17:22.708
- It was so great
seeing you out there, Bethie.

17:22.791 --> 17:25.502
Seeing you up on top,
where you belong.

17:25.586 --> 17:28.088
That coach of yours,
she's doing something right.

17:28.172 --> 17:29.757
- That's what everyone seems
to think.

17:29.840 --> 17:33.260
- You don't like her.
- Don't trust her.

17:33.343 --> 17:36.305
- That tracks.

17:36.388 --> 17:38.599
That tracks.
- What do you mean?

17:38.682 --> 17:40.642
- Did I tell you
I saw her once?

17:40.726 --> 17:42.519
About a week or two ago,

17:42.603 --> 17:44.563
before I knew who she was.

17:44.646 --> 17:48.150
Pretty blonde, standing outside
a convenience store.

17:48.233 --> 17:49.735
Couldn't even light
her own cigarette.

17:49.818 --> 17:51.403
Her hands were shaking so bad.

17:51.487 --> 17:54.490
I played Sir Galahad.
- Good Samaritan.

17:54.573 --> 17:57.743
- [laughs]
I wanted to help her out.

17:57.826 --> 18:00.370
She reminded me
of someone I once knew.

18:00.454 --> 18:03.457
Someone so beautiful
and so hungry

18:03.540 --> 18:06.668
that she thought she should
get everything she wanted.

18:06.752 --> 18:09.922
People like that are dangerous.

18:10.005 --> 18:11.757
- Dangerous?

18:11.840 --> 18:14.343
- Because...

18:14.426 --> 18:16.303
the beauty goes away,

18:16.386 --> 18:20.140
but the hunger only grows

18:20.224 --> 18:23.685
and nobody gets
everything they want.

18:23.769 --> 18:27.481
You gotta decide
what's worth keeping...

18:27.564 --> 18:31.360
and what's worth trading.

18:31.443 --> 18:34.363
<i>[Pisces' "Dear One"]</i>

18:34.446 --> 18:39.159
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:39.243 --> 18:43.872
<i>- ♪ Dear one ♪</i>

18:43.956 --> 18:50.504
<i>♪ Is there anything</i>
<i>you need? ♪</i>

18:53.298 --> 18:58.345
<i>♪ Dear one ♪</i>

18:58.428 --> 19:04.434
<i>♪ Tell me your dream ♪</i>

19:06.895 --> 19:13.610
<i>♪ Somewhere there waits</i>
<i>a golden day ♪</i>

19:13.694 --> 19:20.409
<i>♪ Tell me your dream ♪</i>

19:20.492 --> 19:22.494
<i>♪ Tell me your dream ♪</i>

19:22.578 --> 19:25.164
- Listen, I'm really sorry
I can't make the game tonight.

19:25.247 --> 19:27.958
- It's okay.
I get it.

19:28.041 --> 19:31.253
- It's just--we're all
pulling double shifts now,

19:31.336 --> 19:34.089
with everything.

19:34.173 --> 19:36.091
- Yeah.

19:36.175 --> 19:38.635
<i>[tense music]</i>

19:38.719 --> 19:39.803
Bye.

19:39.887 --> 19:46.894
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:55.444 --> 19:57.446
- How is it possible
that we've never actually met?

19:57.529 --> 20:00.282
- [laughs] Well, it sure feels
like we already have.

20:00.365 --> 20:02.451
I mean, Addy talks about you
all the time.

20:02.534 --> 20:04.620
You've had a big impact on her.

20:04.703 --> 20:07.414
- I'm--I'm glad.

20:09.583 --> 20:11.543
You know, she's so talented.

20:11.627 --> 20:12.961
So disciplined.

20:13.045 --> 20:14.838
Few girls her age have that.

20:14.922 --> 20:17.674
She must get it from you.

20:17.758 --> 20:19.134
- Maybe.
[chuckles]

20:19.218 --> 20:21.053
Though I've never been past
the county limits,

20:21.136 --> 20:24.223
and Addy is just itching
to get out there

20:24.306 --> 20:27.643
in that big, bad world.

20:27.726 --> 20:30.354
- You're worried about her.
I get that.

20:31.897 --> 20:35.901
But I guess that
there's trouble everywhere.

20:35.984 --> 20:38.195
God, I mean, look what happened
to that recruiter

20:38.278 --> 20:40.489
right here in Sutton Grove.

20:40.572 --> 20:41.615
- I'm aware.

20:41.698 --> 20:43.492
- This is the first place
that I've been

20:43.575 --> 20:46.286
that had recruiters stationed
right in the school.

20:46.370 --> 20:49.373
There was something
unnerving about it.

20:49.456 --> 20:52.042
I mean, the one who died,
he seemed okay,

20:52.125 --> 20:55.671
but the other one...

20:55.754 --> 20:58.715
I--I think his name
was Kurtz...

20:58.799 --> 21:00.133
<i>[dark music]</i>

21:00.217 --> 21:02.177
I didn't like what I saw.

21:02.261 --> 21:04.805
- What did you see?

21:04.888 --> 21:07.557
- Attentions.

21:07.641 --> 21:09.476
To my girls.

21:09.559 --> 21:10.936
I told them
to keep their distance.

21:11.019 --> 21:14.648
I hope they did, but...

21:14.731 --> 21:17.025
I heard things.

21:17.109 --> 21:19.778
- Is that right?

21:19.861 --> 21:22.864
- I look out for my girls.

21:22.948 --> 21:26.702
That age, all that beauty,
all that longing...

21:26.785 --> 21:29.413
It is so easy

21:29.496 --> 21:32.291
to find yourself
in dark places.

21:32.374 --> 21:39.381
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:58.233 --> 21:59.776
- I'm surprised
you wanted to talk to me.

21:59.860 --> 22:01.403
- I don't.

22:01.486 --> 22:03.739
Ever.

22:03.822 --> 22:06.325
So cut to the chase.

22:06.408 --> 22:08.785
I know
your dirty little secret.

22:11.455 --> 22:15.375
You've been squatting
at The Towers, haven't you?

22:15.459 --> 22:17.919
In that model apartment.

22:18.003 --> 22:20.339
Across from Sarge Will's.

22:20.422 --> 22:21.798
You don't really live there.

22:24.009 --> 22:26.261
- Who cares?
[laughs]

22:26.345 --> 22:27.471
That building's a ghost town.

22:27.554 --> 22:30.432
- Well, one more ghost now.

22:30.515 --> 22:32.768
So you're gonna tell me

22:32.851 --> 22:35.729
everything you heard
that night.

22:35.812 --> 22:37.147
The night Sarge Will bit it.

22:37.230 --> 22:39.066
- I didn't hear
a goddamn thing.

22:39.149 --> 22:41.568
- No, those walls
are paper thin.

22:43.153 --> 22:45.113
You said so yourself.

22:45.197 --> 22:48.158
So thin,
you couldn't take me there...

22:49.409 --> 22:53.080
'Cause the neighbors
might hear me scream.

22:57.209 --> 23:00.754
Well, it turns out no one did,

23:00.837 --> 23:04.049
that night at the Playland.

23:09.888 --> 23:13.600
We teenage girls
and our selfies.

23:13.683 --> 23:16.186
- Look, I--I can--
I--I was drunk.

23:16.269 --> 23:17.729
I--I didn't--
I don't know--

23:17.813 --> 23:20.107
I--I didn't.
- You did.

23:24.319 --> 23:27.531
So either you start talking...

23:29.032 --> 23:31.368
Or I do.

23:31.451 --> 23:35.080
And I won't ever stop.

23:35.163 --> 23:38.458
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:40.961 --> 23:43.797
[bell rings]

23:43.880 --> 23:46.925
<i>[tense music]</i>

23:47.008 --> 23:51.555
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:51.638 --> 23:53.682
- Look who's joining
the party.

23:53.765 --> 23:55.267
- What's going on?

23:55.350 --> 23:57.644
- Corporal Kurtz here
shares my opinion

23:57.727 --> 23:59.604
of our esteemed coach.

23:59.688 --> 24:00.939
Tell her.

24:01.022 --> 24:03.191
Tell her what you just told me.

24:03.275 --> 24:05.986
She needs to start facing
some hard truths.

24:06.069 --> 24:09.364
Everything in life can't always
be clean and pretty.

24:09.447 --> 24:11.533
Go ahead, spill.

24:12.701 --> 24:15.704
- [sighs]
I'd heard them before,

24:15.787 --> 24:17.247
even saw her a few times.

24:17.330 --> 24:20.834
Once by the elevators,
looking through the peephole.

24:20.917 --> 24:24.171
Sunday night,
I was coming home around 11.

24:24.254 --> 24:25.964
Walked down that long hall--

24:26.047 --> 24:28.967
that's how
I could hear them inside.

24:29.050 --> 24:31.261
Something didn't sound right.

24:32.971 --> 24:34.890
It was mostly shouting.

24:34.973 --> 24:37.392
A lot...of shouting.

24:37.475 --> 24:39.603
I thought something may be up.

24:39.686 --> 24:42.606
He sounded...ragged.

24:44.357 --> 24:46.860
But then it was just like
it usually was.

24:46.943 --> 24:48.945
[pounding]

24:50.572 --> 24:53.158
Headboard banging
like a jackhammer.

24:53.241 --> 24:55.619
[laughs]
Fuck.

24:55.702 --> 24:57.829
I left.

24:57.913 --> 25:00.040
To be honest, I--

25:00.123 --> 25:03.126
the two of them,
it made me sad.

25:04.336 --> 25:06.087
I mean, it was
a fucked up situation.

25:06.171 --> 25:07.214
You could tell

25:07.297 --> 25:08.965
that something bad
was gonna happen.

25:09.049 --> 25:10.717
Things running that hot--

25:10.800 --> 25:12.385
I'm not saying that

25:12.469 --> 25:14.763
she did something to him--
- You are.

25:17.724 --> 25:19.684
- Well, he's obviously lying.

25:19.768 --> 25:21.811
- No, I'm not.

25:21.895 --> 25:24.898
And I'm not saying she--

25:24.981 --> 25:27.317
[sighs]
I just didn't like it.

25:27.400 --> 25:29.027
Hearing them.

25:30.362 --> 25:33.657
I bailed, made my way
to a bar down the road

25:33.740 --> 25:36.701
before any gunshot.

25:36.785 --> 25:39.204
I--I had my problems
with the Sarge.

25:39.287 --> 25:41.581
A lot of 'em.

25:41.665 --> 25:43.875
But he didn't deserve
to go out like that.

25:43.959 --> 25:46.920
He was all caught up in her.

25:47.003 --> 25:50.799
And--and she--
- We know what she's like.

25:50.882 --> 25:52.884
The effect she can have
on people.

26:00.684 --> 26:02.811
- Is this over?

26:02.894 --> 26:04.771
- It's over.

26:04.854 --> 26:06.606
It's over for you.

26:06.690 --> 26:12.487
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:12.570 --> 26:13.905
Get out.

26:20.704 --> 26:21.705
[door shuts]

26:21.788 --> 26:25.417
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:25.500 --> 26:28.378
- What the hell's
wrong with you?

26:28.461 --> 26:30.171
Why are you talking to him?

26:30.255 --> 26:32.757
- Wake up, Addy.

26:32.841 --> 26:36.094
You can lie to everyone else,

26:36.177 --> 26:38.263
but you can't lie to me.

26:40.223 --> 26:42.100
Truth will out.

26:42.183 --> 26:49.190
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:52.527 --> 26:55.447
<i>[dreamy synth music]</i>

26:55.530 --> 27:02.537
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:30.315 --> 27:37.322
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:44.829 --> 27:48.666
<i>[Robotanists' "Warpath"]</i>
<i>- ♪ Hi ♪</i>

27:48.750 --> 27:52.670
<i>♪ Hi ♪</i>

27:52.754 --> 27:55.965
<i>♪ Hi ♪</i>

27:56.049 --> 27:57.967
<i>♪ Hi ♪</i>

27:58.051 --> 27:59.886
<i>♪ Hi ♪</i>

27:59.969 --> 28:01.012
<i>[Sleater-Kinney's</i>
<i>"Surface Envy"]</i>

28:01.096 --> 28:03.348
[chanting]
Eagles! Eagles! Eagles!

28:03.431 --> 28:06.476
